functional_data.summary: The putative functional deficiency caused by TTR M119 should be most marked in the homozygotes.

variants.segregation_data: Future family studies can determine whether the heterozygous state for TTR M119 cosegregates with a disease or trait.
variants.additional_notes: The M119 variant does not cause FAP.
key_quotes: The putative functional deficiency caused by TTR M119 should be most marked in the homozygotes.
Although the nature (if any) of disease caused by TTR M119 remains to be defined, the genetic and clinical data indicate that this mutation does not cause FAP.
